We are excited to provide weekly curbside meal pick-up for our online students. This service is only available for students enrolled in Shelley Online School. Meals WILL be charged to the student's meal account according to the student's meal eligibility status. Please be sure to get your meal applications in.

To receive meals parents/guardians need to submit a weekly order for each student using the link provided. You will need the student ID# for each student.

The first order is due by THIS WEDNESDAY NOON (it will be 9am after this week) WITH PICK UP THIS THURSDAY FROM 10AM TO 10:30AM AT STUART.

Please go to our web page linked below for all the info!
https://shelleyschoolfoodservice.com/index.php…

If you have questions or concerns please call us 208.357.7435

Bus Information - Please help spread the word.

Due to Covid, students will not be allowed to switch seats once they are seated on the bus. They must remain in the seat they choose when first getting on the bus until they reach their destination. We ask that parents please help encourage your children to follow this rule so we can minimize exposure. Face masks are optional but encouraged and our buses will be sanitized daily. All buses will run their regular routes daily (unless we go into red).

ATTENTION!!! (PLEASE SHARE)

All players, we will be suspending all football related activities including the weight room for two weeks. This is because one of our athletes who attended two days of football camp has tested positive for COVID-19. We are currently working with the district health department about the next steps and will have more information in the next 24 hours. This will include what steps the players and coaches will need to take. If you have further questions please email me at jwells@shelleyschools.org.

We will start up activities again on AUG 10th which is the first day of practice

Thanks,

Coach Wells

The Idaho High School Activities Association, in response to COVID-19, has SUSPENDED all sanctioned sports and activities for member schools effective Tuesday March 17th through Sunday April 5th.

The suspension includes:
- No contests, games, or meets at any location.
- No practices at any location.
- No meetings at any location.
- No use of athletic facilities regardless of affiliation (club or otherwise).

post_text: Teacher David Mirhadi was recognized as Employee of the month during the November School Board Meeting. Principal Jared Heath says this about him: “Mr. Mirhadi is Mr. Positive at Stuart Elementary. He is always looking for ways to make the school a better place for kids, teachers, and everyone. On top of his regular teaching duties, he has played a supporting role in helping with the Stuart Stars Awards and is willing to do whatever he can to help the school. One example of this is that he has been anonymously bringing doughnuts and muffins into the staff room on Fridays for the teachers. The teachers eventually caught on and posted a "shout out" in the copy room. He often puts the kids and teachers before himself and is a positive influence on everyone in the school.”
